\begin_layout Section
Unfolding
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A signal enhanced phase space containing less background contributions can
 be selected by a multivariate discriminator from MC and data.
 However the calculation of the top quark spin asymmetries from the resulting
 
\begin_inset Formula ${\textstyle \frac{\mathrm{d}\sigma}{\mathrm{d}\cos\theta_{\mathrm{B,\, X}}}}$
\end_inset

-distributions can not yet be compared to the theory prediction.
 This is due to the smearing effects, finite resolution, the acceptance
 of the detector and from the conducted selections criteria that change
 the differential 
\begin_inset Formula ${\textstyle \frac{\mathrm{d}\sigma}{\mathrm{d}\cos\theta_{\mathrm{B,\, X}}}}$
\end_inset

-shape.
 Unfolding is a method to correct for these effects in a measured distribution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Introduction
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
